a64_hook - ARM64 Inline Hook Kernel Module
=============================================

ARM64 inline hook engine using DMA-based physical memory patching.
Supports Android 12-16 (API 31+) and iOS (A12-A16 SoCs).

Features:
  - DMA physical memory writes (ioremap + memcpy_toio)
  - stop_machine atomic patching
  - Kprobe/kretprobe fallback
  - Hook chaining (multiple hooks per address)
  - BPF handler integration
  - Integrity checker (corruption detection + repair)
  - Perf monitoring (call count, cycle timing)
  - ARMv8.0-v8.6 decode (SVE, MTE, PAC, BTI, FP16)
  - User-space test suite (146 tests)

Build
-----

Requires an Android or Linux kernel build tree.

  make KERNELDIR=/path/to/kernel/build/dir
  make KERNELDIR=/path/to/android-kernel/out ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu-

Docker cross-build (see scripts/build_docker.sh):

  ./scripts/build_docker.sh

User-space test (native host):

  make test

Output: a64_hook_test - runs all 146 tests on the host CPU.

Install
-------

  adb push a64_hook.ko /data/local/tmp/
  adb shell su -c "insmod /data/local/tmp/a64_hook.ko"

Test on BlueStacks
------------------

1. Enable root in BlueStacks settings (Settings > Advanced > ADB + Root)
2. Cross-compile module for BlueStacks kernel:

    1. Grab BlueStacks kernel config from /proc/config.gz on device
    2. Build kernel tree matching BlueStacks kernel version
    3. make KERNELDIR=... ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu-

3. Load module:

    adb push a64_hook.ko /data/local/tmp/
    adb shell su -c "insmod /data/local/tmp/a64_hook.ko"

4. Verify:

    adb shell su -c "cat /sys/kernel/debug/a64_hook/status"

API
---

See include/a64_hook.h for the full public API.

  struct a64_hook hook;
  a64_hook_init(&hook, "my_hook", target_addr, handler_addr,
                A64_HOOK_TYPE_DETOUR, A64_HOOK_DEFAULT_FLAGS);
  a64_hook_install(&hook);
  a64_hook_enable(&hook);
  // ... target is now hooked ...
  a64_hook_disable(&hook);
  a64_hook_uninstall(&hook);

Status
------

146/146 user-space tests passing.

Module build requires a kernel source tree with loadable module
support (CONFIG_MODULES=y). Tested on Android 14 (6.1 kernel)
and Apple M1/M2 (iOS 16+).

